  \ mode in allowlist,\n      network in allowlist, image_profile in allowlist,\n\
  \      forbidden options in command)\n\n## MRS concept excerpt\n\nC-003 SandboxPolicy\
  \ / C-010 ContainerRuntime mount modes:\n  - cwd must be relative and resolve inside\
  \ /workspace\n  - Supported modes: read_only (default), workspace_write, scratch_write\n\
  \  - /workspace is always the container mount point; caller cannot choose it\n \
  \ - Mount modes: read_only (ro), workspace_write (rw), scratch_write (ro+scratch\
  \ rw)\n\n## What to add\n\nAdd the following after DEFAULT_POLICY_CONFIG and before\
  \ ValidationResult.\nAlso add build_mount_spec() as a method of SandboxPolicy after\
  \ validate().\n\n### @dataclass(frozen=True) MountSpec  (insert after DEFAULT_POLICY_CONFIG)\n\
  \n```python\n@dataclass(frozen=True)\nclass MountSpec:\n    \"\"\"Validated container\
  \ mount configuration produced by SandboxPolicy.\n\n    Consumed by ContainerRuntime\
  \ (C-010) when creating the container.\n    /workspace is always the mount point;\
  \ callers cannot choose it.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    workspace_source: Path\n    \"\"\"\
